As of the 2020 census, there were 323 people, 143 housing units, and 93 families in the CDP. In Deer Island there were, 282 [[White Americans|White]] people, 0 [[African Americans]], 10 [[Native Americans in the United States|Native Americans]], 2 [[Asian Americans|Asians]], 0 [[Pacific Islander]]s, 6 people that were from some other race, and 23 from two or more races. 30 people were from [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] origin.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Deer_Island_CDP;_Oregon?g=160XX00US4118450 |access-date=2023-05-16 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

The ancestry of Deer Island is 21.8% [[German Americans|German]], 13.8% [[Irish Americans|Irish]], 11.5% [[French Americans|French]], 2.9% [[Italian Americans|Italian]], and 2.9% [[Norwegian Americans|Norwegian]].<ref name=":0" />

The median age in Deer Island was 52.4 years old. 29.3% of the population were over 65, with 22.4% from 65 to 74, and 6.9% from 75 to 84. 0.0% of the population were foreign born.<ref name=":0" />

The median household income was $23,750, with families having $37,500, and non-families having $18,750. 5.2% of the population were in poverty, and 9.9% of people 18 to 64 were in poverty.<ref name=":0" />

